title: Dogs model 'Howl'oween' costumes in Carol Stream
text: Success - Article sent! close Video: Pet parade Giana Ayers of Aurora holds up Calvin, who won the Funniest Costume contest Sunday while dressed as a lobster in a pot, during the Carol Stream Park District's Howl'oween Dog Parade and Costume Contest at the Bark Park. Mark Black | Staff Photographer Fiona Young photographs her daughter Olivia, 11, and their golden retriever Annie in front of the great pumpkin Sunday during the Howl'oween Dog Parade and Costume Contest at Carol Stream Park District's Bark Park. Mark Black | Staff Photographer Chewie came dressed as a scarecrow Sunday at the Carol Stream Park District's Howl'oween Dog Parade and Costume Contest at Bark Park. Mark Black | Staff Photographer Daily Herald report A black cat wouldn't cross this parade. Canines only -- in their Halloween costumes -- strolled with their human companions Sunday in Carol Stream's Dog Park. related advertisement With prizes at stake, the pooches went for the cute, not the spook, factor in the park district's annual Howl'oween dog parade and costume contest. Judges picked winners in categories that had dogs dressing after television and movie characters or, with their two-legged friends, vying for cutest couple. And because modeling Halloween costumes is tough work, dogs were pampered with bobbing for Howl'oweenies and other treats. Share this page
